in ApacheRequest___parse() of src/apache-2/apache_request.c there is this fragment of code:

    if ((r->method_number == M_POST) && ct && strncaseEQ(ct, MULTIPART_ENCTYPE, MULTIPART_ENCTYPE_LENGTH))
    {
        ap_log_rerror(REQ_INFO, "content-type: `%s'", ct);
        result = ApacheRequest_parse_multipart(req,ct);
    }


That results in a noisy log message that is falsely labelled "Internal error", which unnecessarily causes concern for the user.


[Wed Nov 27 07:58:17 2013] [info] [client 70.42.6.154] (20014)Internal error: content-type: `multipart/form-data', referer: http://flightaware.com/live/flight/VAU1


I propose removing the ap_log_rerror line entirely.
